verbose_text: Although a substantial number of primary grade III glioma samples were found to be IDH mutant on the basis of immunohistochemistry, and to have detectable levels of 2HG, there were other differences in their metabolite profile relative to secondary anaplastic glioma, which included significantly lower levels of the tumor markers Gly XREF_BIBR and PC/GPC.
evidence: levels of the tumor markers Gly  XREF_BIBR  and PC/GPC
